<subSubSection id="02C66578FFE3FFA2FC9599746DF07B2A" pageId="14" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFE3FFA2FC9599746D5378C8" blockId="14.[831,1437,1328,1611]" pageId="14" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE3FFA2FC9599746ABD7829" bold="true" box="[831,944,1328,1352]" pageId="14" pageNumber="28">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species is characterized by the spinose projection of the chambers which came either from the lower angle of the chambers or from the middle of the periphery of the chambers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFE3FFA2FC9599F56DF07B2A" blockId="14.[831,1437,1328,1611]" pageId="14" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE3FFA2FC9599F56D7E78A8" bold="true" box="[831,1139,1457,1481]" pageId="14" pageNumber="28">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It was firstly described in the Late Cretaceous of Central Europe and America. In the study area, it is floody in the Paleocene 
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE3FFA2FAA499B66C1B7B6B" box="[1294,1302,1522,1546]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="28">(</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFE3FFA2FABF99B66D197B4B" authority="Zone" authorityName="Zone" class="Globothalamea" family="Truncorotaloididae" genus="Morozovella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="14" pageNumber="28" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="trinidadensis">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE3FFA2FABF99B66AC77B4A" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="28">Morozovella trinidadensis</emphasis>
Zone
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFE3FFA2FB809A576C687B4B" authority="Zone" authorityName="Zone" box="[1066,1381,1555,1579]" class="Globothalamea" family="Truncorotaloididae" genus="Morozovella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="14" pageNumber="28" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="uncinata">
